  "prompt": "Account opening in Zerodha states 48 hours, I have submitted all documents and it has been 10 days with no luck. Pathetic support, how to escalate?",
  "response": "I understand your frustration with the delay in opening your Zerodha account. Here are some steps you can take to escalate your issue:\n\n1. **Contact Customer Support Again:**\n   - **Email:** Reach out to Zerodha's support team via email at support@zerodha.com. Clearly state your issue, mention that it has been 10 days since you submitted your documents, and request an urgent update on your account status.\n   - **Phone:** You can call their customer support at 080-4718 1888 (available from 8 AM to 8 PM on weekdays). Explain your situation and ask for a resolution.\n\n2. **Use Social Media:**\n   - Platforms like Twitter and LinkedIn can be effective for escalating issues. Send a direct message to Zerodha's official accounts or post publicly about your experience, tagging Zerodha. This often prompts a quicker response.\n\n3. **Grievance Redressal:**\n   - Zerodha has a dedicated grievance redressal mechanism. You can submit a complaint through their website. Navigate to the \"Contact Us\" section and find the grievance form. Fill it out with all necessary details and submit it.\n\n4. **Escalate to Higher Authority:**\n   - If the above steps do not yield results, you can escalate the matter to the National Stock Exchange (NSE) or the Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI). You can file a complaint on their respective websites:\n     - **NSE:** https://www.nseindia.com/invest/customer-feedback\n     - **SEBI:** https://scores.gov.in/scores/Welcome.html\n\n5. **Follow-Up:**\n   - Keep a record of all your communications (emails, call logs, social media interactions) and follow up regularly. Persistence is key in resolving such issues.\n\nHere's a sample email you could send to Zerodha's support:\n\n---\n\nSubject: Urgent: Delay in Account Opening - No Response After 10 Days\n\nDear Zerodha Support Team,\n\nI am writing to express my concern and frustration regarding the delay in opening my trading account. I submitted all required documents 10 days ago and was informed that the process would take about 48 hours. However, I have not received any updates or communications from your end.\n\nMy application reference number is [Insert Reference Number Here]. I kindly request an immediate update on the status of my account and a resolution to this issue.\n\nI have tried reaching out through your customer support channels multiple times but have not received a satisfactory response. If I do not hear back promptly, I will be forced to escalate this matter to higher authorities such as the NSE and SEBI.\n\nThank you for your attention to this urgent matter. I look forward to your swift response.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n[Your Contact Information]\n\n---\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to get a resolution to your issue more quickly.",
